A general view of the outside of a COVID-19 ward at  Hospital in Cape Town. JOHANNESBURG - There have been 1,094 new COVID-19 cases reported in South Africa in the last 24 hours. 15,930 tests were conducted in that period. READ: WHO applauds SA for response in fight against COVID-19 This brings the total number of laboratory-confirmed cases in South Africa to 3,642,925. The National Department of Health has reported 257 deaths and of these, three occurred in the past 24 to 48 hours. This brings the total fatalities to 97,250 to date.